verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, O my soul: and all that is within me, bless his holy name.
verses.verse_html: 1Bless the Lord, O my soul: and all that is within me, bless his holy name.

verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits:
verses.verse_html: 2Bless the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits:

verses.text_plain: Who forgiveth all thine iniquities; who healeth all thy diseases;
verses.verse_html: 3Who forgiveth all thine iniquities; who healeth all thy diseases;

verses.text_plain: Who redeemeth thy life from destruction; who crowneth thee with lovingkindness and tender mercies;
verses.verse_html: 4Who redeemeth thy life from destruction; who crowneth thee with lovingkindness and tender mercies;

verses.text_plain: Who satisfieth thy mouth with good things; so that thy youth is renewed like the eagle’s.
verses.verse_html: 5Who satisfieth thy mouth with good things; so that thy youth is renewed like the eagle’s.

verses.text_plain: The Lord executeth righteousness and judgment for all that are oppressed.
verses.verse_html: 6The Lord executeth righteousness and judgment for all that are oppressed.

verses.text_plain: He made known his ways unto Moses, his acts unto the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 7He made known his ways unto Moses, his acts unto the children of Israel.

verses.text_plain: The Lord is merciful and gracious, slow to anger, and plenteous in mercy.
verses.verse_html:
8The Lord is merciful and gracious, slow to anger, and plenteous in mercy. ▼
▼ plenteous…: Heb. great in mercy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ plenteous…: Heb. great in mercy

verses.text_plain: He will not always chide: neither will he keep his anger for ever.
verses.verse_html: 9He will not always chide: neither will he keep his anger for ever.

verses.text_plain: He hath not dealt with us after our sins; nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.
verses.verse_html: 10He hath not dealt with us after our sins; nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.

verses.text_plain: For as the heaven is high above the earth, so great is his mercy toward them that fear him.
verses.verse_html:
11For as the heaven is high above the earth, so great is his mercy toward them that fear him. ▼
▼ as…: Heb. according to the height of the heaven

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as…: Heb. according to the height of the heaven
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as…: Heb. according to the height of the heaven

verses.text_plain: As far as the east is from the west, so far hath he removed our transgressions from us.
verses.verse_html: 12As far as the east is from the west, so far hath he removed our transgressions from us.

verses.text_plain: Like as a father pitieth his children, so the Lord pitieth them that fear him.
verses.verse_html: 13Like as a father pitieth his children, so the Lord pitieth them that fear him.

verses.text_plain: For he knoweth our frame; he remembereth that we are dust.
verses.verse_html: 14For he knoweth our frame; he remembereth that we are dust.

verses.text_plain: As for man, his days are as grass: as a flower of the field, so he flourisheth.
verses.verse_html: 15As for man, his days are as grass: as a flower of the field, so he flourisheth.

verses.text_plain: For the wind passeth over it, and it is gone; and the place thereof shall know it no more.
verses.verse_html:
16For the wind passeth over it, and it is gone; and the place thereof shall know it no more. ▼
▼ it is…: Heb. it is not

tokens.text: it, and it is gone; and the place

footnotes.body_text: ▼ it is…: Heb. it is not
footnotes.body_html: ▼ it is…: Heb. it is not

verses.text_plain: But the mercy of the Lord is from everlasting to everlasting upon them that fear him, and his righteousness unto children’s children;
verses.verse_html: 17But the mercy of the Lord is from everlasting to everlasting upon them that fear him, and his righteousness unto children’s children;

verses.text_plain: To such as keep his covenant, and to those that remember his commandments to do them.
verses.verse_html: 18To such as keep his covenant, and to those that remember his commandments to do them.

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath prepared his throne in the heavens; and his kingdom ruleth over all.
verses.verse_html: 19The Lord hath prepared his throne in the heavens; and his kingdom ruleth over all.

verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, ye his angels, that excel in strength, that do his commandments, hearkening unto the voice of his word.
verses.verse_html:
20Bless the Lord, ye his angels, that excel in strength, that do his commandments, hearkening unto the voice of his word. ▼
▼ that excel…: Heb. mighty in strength

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that excel…: Heb. mighty in strength
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that excel…: Heb. mighty in strength

verses.text_plain: Bless ye the Lord, all ye his hosts; ye ministers of his, that do his pleasure.
verses.verse_html: 21Bless ye the Lord, all ye his hosts; ye ministers of his, that do his pleasure.

verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, all his works in all places of his dominion: bless the Lord, O my soul.
verses.verse_html: 22Bless the Lord, all his works in all places of his dominion: bless the Lord, O my soul.
